1
00:01:01,800 --> 00:01:02,360
Look.

2
00:01:02,440 --> 00:01:03,640
My sister is back.

3
00:01:08,360 --> 00:01:08,920
Dad.

4
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:18,240
My sister is back.

5
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:37,320
Dad.

6
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:39,720
Where is our rickshaw?

7
00:01:41,039 --> 00:01:42,800
Since you've run away,

8
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:46,160
don't come back home.

9
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:49,400
Go somewhere where no one knows you.

10
00:01:49,759 --> 00:01:51,520
Start a new life.

11
00:02:04,520 --> 00:02:05,160
Sis.

12
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,340
Are you hungry?

13
00:02:56,120 --> 00:02:56,880
Xiao Anzi.

14
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:58,800
Take good care of Dad.

15
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:00,770
I'm not coming back.

16
00:03:04,280 --> 00:03:04,920
Sis.

17
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:21,240
Thank you, Doctor Xu.

18
00:04:27,440 --> 00:04:27,970
Let's go.

19
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:35,640
Feel at ease now?

20
00:04:36,760 --> 00:04:38,400
You heard Doctor Xu.

21
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:40,560
Your father's leg

22
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:41,700
isn't hard to cure.

23
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:43,159
Later,

24
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:45,200
I'll have someone prescribe medicine

25
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:46,600
and send it to him on time.

26
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:48,220
He'll be fine before long.

27
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:50,000
This

28
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:52,320
is the deposit for your first night.

29
00:04:53,159 --> 00:04:54,520
Doctor Xu's fees

30
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:56,610
will be deducted from this.

31
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:59,040
After your debut the day after tomorrow,

32
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:00,840
you won't be a novice anymore.

33
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:03,960
You should thank that patron properly.

34
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:07,040
Have I met that patron?

35
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:10,400
It doesn't matter if you've met him.

36
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:12,200
He paid the deposit,

37
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:14,050
so naturally he favors you.

38
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:38,600
Judging by the victim's weight,

39
00:06:39,520 --> 00:06:41,380
Yingtao couldn't move him at all.

40
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:43,360
So Yingtao couldn't have

41
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:45,280
placed the victim on the box,

42
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:47,880
then opened a crack to crawl inside herself.

43
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:50,360
If it's as Yingtao said,

44
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:52,760
that after she got into the box,

45
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:55,440
the killer stabbed the victim,

46
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:59,760
then why did the killer lock the box?

47
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,460
Because only by locking it

48
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:05,680
could he prove that Yingtao couldn't have killed him.

49
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:06,800
You mean

50
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:09,600
he didn't want us to suspect Yingtao?

51
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:13,200
Then why didn't he take her with him?

52
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:25,660
Because leaving would make things even harder to explain.

53
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:29,840
If it wasn't Yingtao,

54
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:32,520
how did the killer get out?

55
00:07:33,880 --> 00:07:35,810
Did they use an earth escape spell?

56
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:39,440
I've only read about

57
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:41,120
locked-room murders in books.

58
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:43,120
I never thought I'd see one for real.

59
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:46,000
"Locked-room murder."

60
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:49,280
That describes it perfectly.

61
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:53,320
It was around 3:00 a.m.

62
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:55,760
I heard noises in my room,

63
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:58,200
but saw no one when I got up.

64
00:07:58,600 --> 00:07:59,120
But

65
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:00,860
the clothes I put by the bed

66
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:02,570
were thrown onto the floor.

67
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:04,240
Me too.

68
00:08:04,240 --> 00:08:05,640
I heard footsteps at night,

69
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:06,920
but no one was there.

70
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:08,320
Is it haunted?

71
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:09,920
The pastries in my room

72
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:12,000
mysteriously went missing this morning.

73
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,960
I thought a rat took them.

74
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:16,820
Xiaotaohong's bracelet is missing too.

75
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:19,210
A rat couldn't have taken that, right?

76
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:21,880
If

77
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:23,840
Yingtao didn't kill him,

78
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:25,960
is the killer still hiding here?

79
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:28,400
The Inspector is handling the case.

80
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:30,560
It's not your place.

81
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:36,400
Who switched my wine with water?

82
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:37,200
Wang Guilan.

83
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:38,440
Position.

84
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:39,880
Concubine.

85
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:41,159
Concubine?

86
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:43,120
Just a bottom-tier concubine.

87
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:44,000
A drinking substitute.

88
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:46,130
Do whatever you want when she's drunk.

89
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:49,000
I wouldn't be interested in you even if I were drunk.

90
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,280
I'll beat you to death.

91
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:51,960
What's all the noise?

92
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:52,680
And you?

93
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:54,680
Is there anyone here

94
00:08:54,680 --> 00:08:56,320
who used to be a carpenter

95
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:57,860
or knows how to fix things?

96
00:08:58,760 --> 00:09:00,840
Everything here is an antique.

97
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:02,600
They can't fix them.

98
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:05,500
We always find carpenters from outside.

99
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:07,900
Have you hired a carpenter recently?

100
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,520
Nothing is broken.

101
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:12,740
Why would we need a carpenter?

102
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:16,320
They are all just yes-men.

103
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:18,520
If they had the guts to kill,

104
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:21,680
they wouldn't be doing this servile work.

105
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:24,480
Who is she?

106
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:26,360
She is the top talent here,

107
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,120
named Guan Sinian.

108
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:30,840
She is the so-called top courtesan.

109
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,330
But she has a bad temper.

110
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:33,440
Madam,

111
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:35,000
someone entered my bathroom

112
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,360
and took a bath inside.

113
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:14,320
It must be a man.

114
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:16,320
The stove is cold.

115
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:17,920
It's been off for a few hours.

116
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:19,800
Who usually uses this bathroom?

117
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:21,330
I'm the only one who uses it.

118
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:56,620
Inspector.

119
00:10:56,880 --> 00:10:58,480
I think he's long gone.

120
00:10:59,040 --> 00:11:00,970
Could you withdraw your officers?

121
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:02,720
It's mainly about tomorrow's event.

122
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:04,650
The deposit has already been paid.

123
00:11:04,920 --> 00:11:06,120
This is a crime scene.

124
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:07,400
Until the truth is out,

125
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:09,000
you have a duty to cooperate.

126
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:10,560
No, but you can't stop us from doing business

127
00:11:10,560 --> 00:11:11,760
just because some sick ghost died,

128
00:11:11,760 --> 00:11:13,160
right?

129
00:11:13,560 --> 00:11:14,040
You...

130
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:22,640
I think Boss Qin is right.

131
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:25,440
If the killer were normal,

132
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:26,280
he would have fled long ago.

133
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:27,740
Why would he still be here?

134
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:30,120
Go.

135
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:31,890
Withdraw everyone.

136
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,440
He didn't leave after killing someone.

137
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:43,080
He stole snacks and wine,

138
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:43,920
and even took a bath.

139
00:11:43,920 --> 00:11:45,520
Is he making himself at home?

140
00:11:46,240 --> 00:11:48,360
I guess the killer is still in the courtyard.

141
00:11:48,360 --> 00:11:50,320
He won't make a move if we watch too closely.

142
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:51,050
Brother Bao.

143
00:11:51,160 --> 00:11:52,680
Get a group of plainclothes officers over here.

144
00:11:52,680 --> 00:11:54,000
Make sure they're disguised well

145
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,130
and guard the exits.

146
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:08,120
The victim died from a sharp object piercing the lung,

147
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:09,200
causing massive bleeding

148
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,530
and hemopneumothorax.

149
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,000
The murder weapon

150
00:12:12,040 --> 00:12:13,080
is this chisel.

151
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:22,280
Meningeal hyperplasia.

152
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:23,680
Typical gumma.

153
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:26,240
It's tertiary neurosyphilis.

154
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:28,560
It means the victim had syphilis

155
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:30,000
for at least a decade.

156
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:31,560
And symptoms like

157
00:12:31,560 --> 00:12:32,200
dementia,

158
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:33,040
madness,

159
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:34,680
and cognitive decline had already appeared.

160
00:12:34,680 --> 00:12:36,640
That matches what Yingtao said.

161
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:39,810
The victim was only about nineteen years old.

162
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:40,880
You mean

163
00:12:41,160 --> 00:12:44,090
he was infected with syphilis when he was very young?

164
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,000
The victim's face

165
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:46,880
was deliberately disfigured

166
00:12:46,880 --> 00:12:48,000
after death.

167
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:49,800
To find the killer,

168
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,440
we must first figure out

169
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:53,040
who the victim is.

170
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:55,200
The victim had syphilis for years

171
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:57,040
and needed long-term medication.

172
00:12:57,040 --> 00:12:59,480
There should be a regular doctor prescribing the medicine.

173
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:00,480
Leave that to me.

174
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:02,080
Bao.

175
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:05,160
Focus on screening patients with dementia

176
00:13:05,160 --> 00:13:06,490
and cognitive decline.

177
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:07,810
Don't worry.

178
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:11,720
Congmingdou.

179
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:15,640
Call the porter from Lianxi Tower back for questioning.

180
00:13:15,640 --> 00:13:17,680
If he is the only one with the key,

181
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:19,560
he probably didn't tell the truth.

182
00:13:19,560 --> 00:13:20,120
Yes, sir.

183
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:21,100
Inspector Lin.

184
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,560
Wang Deshun from Lianxi Tower has run away.

185
00:13:23,560 --> 00:13:24,620
Who is Wang Deshun?

186
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:26,370
He is the porter from there.

187
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:05,760
Listen to me.

188
00:14:06,880 --> 00:14:07,810
Listen closely.

189
00:14:09,080 --> 00:14:10,360
The triangular one

190
00:14:10,560 --> 00:14:11,720
is mixed with ash.

191
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:13,400
The square one

192
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:14,530
is the Fushou paste.

193
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:16,680
If you get it wrong again,

194
00:14:17,040 --> 00:14:18,840
you can forget about your wages.

195
00:14:22,680 --> 00:14:24,000
The triangle is fake.

196
00:14:24,520 --> 00:14:25,600
The square is real.

197
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:27,160
Fake.

198
00:14:27,760 --> 00:14:28,320
Real.

199
00:14:28,560 --> 00:14:29,520
Shut up.

200
00:14:30,560 --> 00:14:31,480
Yesterday,

201
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:33,800
which one did you give that brothel lackey?

202
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:35,480
It... it was the mixed one.

203
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:36,800
I'm sure of it.

204
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:38,480
Good.

205
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:39,400
Go away.

206
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:46,880
This piece of trash

207
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:48,840
wants opium paste?

208
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:50,160
In his dreams.

209
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:52,680
Feeding good stuff to a dog?

210
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:54,320
It's a pure waste.

211
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:05,640
This nineteen-year-old...

212
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:10,160
Let me ask you,

213
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:12,880
has any nineteen-year-old been treated here?

214
00:15:13,880 --> 00:15:15,160
Plenty of them.

215
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,400
What illness do you have?

216
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:19,840
I can cure any difficult disease.

217
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:23,520
Syphilis.

218
00:15:23,520 --> 00:15:24,680
Had it since childhood.

219
00:15:24,680 --> 00:15:26,880
Have you treated anyone like that here?

220
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:28,480
I can cure it.

221
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:31,800
A mix of Chinese and Western medicine guarantees survival.

222
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:33,080
Simazi's son

223
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:34,840
was treated right here.

224
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:40,120
Put it on.

225
00:15:41,760 --> 00:15:42,760
How old is his son?

226
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:44,720
Also nineteen.

227
00:15:45,240 --> 00:15:46,880
Infected since childhood.

228
00:15:46,880 --> 00:15:47,680
Where is Simazi's home?

229
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:49,160
Where is he? Where does he live?

230
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:50,240
Jianye Lane,

231
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:51,880
Sixi Opium Den.

232
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:53,840
If you don't believe me,

233
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:55,360
go see for yourself.

234
00:15:58,680 --> 00:15:59,740
Where is everyone?

235
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:01,560
I don't know.

236
00:16:09,160 --> 00:16:11,690
Do you know which opium den he usually goes to?

237
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:13,360
I think it's

238
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:14,920
Sixi Opium Den.

239
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:26,880
Deshun,

240
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:28,960
I figured you'd be back by now.

241
00:16:30,880 --> 00:16:31,740
Where is my son?

242
00:16:32,280 --> 00:16:33,080
In the back.

243
00:16:37,360 --> 00:16:38,520
For our Shitao,

244
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:39,840
it was worth it.

245
00:16:40,720 --> 00:16:42,240
I really must thank you.

246
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:27,920
It is highly likely that he opened the door

247
00:17:27,920 --> 00:17:29,120
and brought the victim inside.

248
00:17:29,120 --> 00:17:30,640
Running away now is definitely suspicious.

249
00:17:30,640 --> 00:17:31,680
Let's find him first.
